@@aPALADIN@@W

@@aHistory@@W
  The Paladin order arose from the aftermath of the Sundering Wars, when the
  gods themselves were said to have wept at the desecration of their temples
  by mortal armies. Several high clerics, unwilling to leave their sanctuaries
  defenseless again, forsook pure ministry and took up arms without abandoning
  their faith. They swore binding oaths -- not to any king or nation, but to
  the light itself -- and trained in armored combat under the doctrines of
  advance and sanctification. The first Paladins served as shield-wardens at
  the great temples, holding every threshold against the dark. Their oath-
  marks, inscribed in holy silver, are said to burn cold when an enemy of the
  faith draws near.

Paladins are oathbound vanguards who turn faith into forward pressure. Their
style is direct: close distance, hold formation, and punish evil with sanctified
steel.

